<item>
            <title>[LU-10648] Lustre should not do ldlm_resource_dump to console in case of an eviction</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10648</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During an eviction, Lustre calls ldlm_namespace_cleanup, and it will sometimes end up dumping all of the locks on a particular resource to the console log (ldlm_resource_complain), which is very wasteful and only rarely helpful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Move the debug level for this to D_DLMTRACE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
